39:24.696 --> 39:27.446
[sighs]
I love you.

39:27.490 --> 39:29.950
I’ve thought about you
every day of your life.

39:29.993 --> 39:33.623
And if you ever need me,
I’m here for you.

39:33.663 --> 39:37.793
And if you never need me,
that’s okay, too.

39:37.834 --> 39:40.804
It’s not your job
to worry about me.

39:40.837 --> 39:43.167
I’ll be fine.

39:43.214 --> 39:44.634
And I’ll still love you.

39:44.674 --> 39:46.634
- [breathes shakily]

39:46.676 --> 39:48.636
So...

39:48.678 --> 39:50.178
that’s it.

39:50.221 --> 39:52.641
[sentimental music]

39:52.682 --> 39:54.352
- All right.

39:54.392 --> 39:56.142
- All right.

39:56.185 --> 39:59.515
♪ ♪

39:59.564 --> 40:02.944
[sighs happily]

40:02.984 --> 40:04.994
- Hello?

40:05.028 --> 40:06.278
D’arcy?

40:10.867 --> 40:14.157
[door closes]

40:14.203 --> 40:16.873
Hey. D’arcy?

40:16.915 --> 40:20.335
- [gasps, chuckles]
Oh, hey.

40:20.376 --> 40:22.706
Hey.

40:22.754 --> 40:25.424
What’s going on?
- I don’t know. You tell me.

40:25.465 --> 40:27.015
It’s 1:00 in the morning.

40:27.050 --> 40:29.340
Were you really gonna sleep
in here with the door unlocked?

40:29.385 --> 40:32.095
- Um, I was just cleaning up.
I lost track of time.

40:32.138 --> 40:33.638
- Really?

40:33.681 --> 40:35.561
’Cause it looked like you were
sleeping on the pool table.

40:35.600 --> 40:37.100
- You gonna tell me
where to sleep now?

40:37.143 --> 40:38.443
- Okay.
- Wait, wait.

40:38.478 --> 40:40.518
- We had plans.

40:40.563 --> 40:43.483
I waited for two hours.

40:43.524 --> 40:45.034
Maybe I should just take
a hint.

40:45.068 --> 40:46.568
- No.

40:46.611 --> 40:48.321
- Obviously you’re not taking
me or any of this seriously.

40:48.363 --> 40:50.203
- I feel like you’re
being a little dramatic.

40:50.239 --> 40:52.369
- If you care even just
a little bit about me,

40:52.408 --> 40:54.788
you need to tell me
what’s really going on.

40:57.580 --> 40:59.080
Please?

40:59.123 --> 41:00.883
It’s okay.
- [stammers]

41:00.917 --> 41:02.707
It’s fine, all right?

41:02.752 --> 41:05.132
Just--let me just grab
my stuff, and we can go.

41:05.171 --> 41:06.341
- No.

41:07.840 --> 41:11.010
- What do you mean--
what do you mean "no"?

41:11.052 --> 41:14.312
- I think it’s best
if we just leave it at this.

41:14.347 --> 41:16.387
- Elliot, like...

41:16.432 --> 41:17.732
no.

41:17.767 --> 41:20.727
[somber music]

41:20.770 --> 41:23.060
♪ ♪

41:23.106 --> 41:25.726
Don’t...

41:25.775 --> 41:27.445
Please don’t go.

41:27.485 --> 41:31.405
♪ ♪

41:31.447 --> 41:34.407
- [sighs]

41:34.450 --> 41:36.450
[sobs]

41:36.494 --> 41:38.624
♪ ♪

41:38.663 --> 41:40.293
- Bye, D’arcy.

41:40.331 --> 41:47.171
♪ ♪

41:47.213 --> 41:50.513
It’s probably best
if you lock up behind me.

41:50.550 --> 41:54.090
♪ ♪

41:54.137 --> 41:56.467
- [sobs]

41:56.514 --> 41:58.224
[grunts]

42:01.561 --> 42:04.441
[Brian Eno and David Byrne’s
"One Fine Day"]

42:04.480 --> 42:06.610
- It is natural for aliens
to take control

42:06.649 --> 42:08.149
of their lives.

42:08.192 --> 42:10.902
It is not so natural
for humans.

42:10.945 --> 42:18.035
♪ ♪

42:24.500 --> 42:26.630
- [crying]

42:26.669 --> 42:28.249
- [sighs]

42:28.296 --> 42:32.166
- ♪ Saw the wanderin’ eye ♪

42:32.216 --> 42:34.836
♪ Inside my heart ♪

42:34.886 --> 42:38.506
